    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, preserved in museum-quality condition. This specimen features the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine, exhibiting factory-spec compression across all rotor faces. The sequential twin-turbocharger system transitions seamlessly at 4,500 RPM, free of the typical boost-pattern fluctuations. The chassis retains its surgical precision via an all-aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential. Unmodified and structurally perfect, the vehicle benefits from a pristine cooling system and intact vacuum line routing, ensuring thermal efficiency. The five-speed manual transmission provides positive engagement with no synchro grind. This is a rare, unmolested example of 50/50 weight distribution engineering.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
